<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-2298] Client Selector can drop connections on InvalidReceiveException without notifying NetworkClient</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2298</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I run into the problem described in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2266&quot; title=&quot;Client Selector can drop idle connections without notifying NetworkClient&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-2266&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-2266&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; when testing quota. I was told the bug was fixed in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2266&quot; title=&quot;Client Selector can drop idle connections without notifying NetworkClient&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-2266&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-2266&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; after I figured out the problem.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;But the patch provided in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-2266&quot; title=&quot;Client Selector can drop idle connections without notifying NetworkClient&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-2266&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-2266&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; probably doesn&apos;t solve all related problems. From reading the code there is still one edge case where the client selector can close connection in poll() without notifying NetworkClient.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
